               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa gǝnzat “Book of the Funeral Ritual” (fols. 3ra-127vb)&#xD; -
                     Discourse of St Athanasius on death (fols. 3ra-13ra)&#xD; - Maṣḥaf za-wäḍʾat
                     ʾǝm-ʾIyarusalem “Book that came from Jerusalem” (fols. 13va-21ra)&#xD; - Homily
                     by ʾabbā Salāmā, Metropolitan of Ethiopia (fols. 90rb-93rb)&#xD; - Antiphons
                     (ʾaryām, mawāśǝʾt and mǝlṭān) (fols. 122vb-127vb)&#xD; II) Maṣḥafa ʾardǝʾt
                     “Book of the Disciples” (fols. 128ra-149rb)&#xD; &#xD; Colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><title>Maṣḥafa gǝnzat</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2"><title>Maṣḥafa ʾardǝʾt</title>
                     
                     
                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                        <locus target="#149rb">149rb</locus>: ስብሐት፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ ዘአፈጸመኒ፡ ጽሒፈ፡ መጽሐፎሙ፡
                        ለ፲ወ፪አርድእት፡ አነ፡ ኃጥእ፡ ወጊጉይ፡ ወልደ፡ ሥላሴ።<locus target="#149rb">149rb</locus>: May
                        praise be to God who made me finish the writing of the Book of the 12
                        Disciples. I am sinner and wicked Walda Śǝllāse. The colophon mentions Walda
                        Śǝllāse as the scribe only for Text I. </colophon>
                  </msItem>
                  
