                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors in Text I; names
                           of the commissioner and the scribe in Text II; a few lines in the incipit
                           pages of Text I and II, alternating with black lines; two initial lines
                           of each section of the text Text I and II; some abbreviations, elements
                           of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numbers; some other words,
                           e.g., ṣällǝyu (e.g., fols. 10va, 11rb, 15ra), tagśāṣ (fol. 22rb), salām
                           (fols. 80va, 125ra), wa-ʾǝmzǝ (e.g., fols. 83vb, 84rb, 86rb), mǝlṭān
                           (e.g., fols. 125ra, 126ra, 127ra).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Hand a: <locus from="3ra" to="127vb">3ra-127vb</locus>; the quality of handwriting changes (e.g., <locus target="#114r">114r</locus>).<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic"> Hand b (Walda Śǝllāse): <locus from="128ra" to="149rb">128ra-149rb</locus>; the handwriting appears
                        uneven with broadly spaced and right-sloping letters. The scribe sometimes
                        disregards the ruling line (e.g.,
